table.body:
If you own a property and want to change its ownership (eg if you're transferring it into another person's name, or if you want to add your partner as a joint owner), you need to register this with the Land Registry.

s1. Download and fill out [form AP1 'Application to change the register' (PDF, 162KB).](http://www.landregistry.gov.uk/_media/downloads/forms/AP1.pdf "Form AP1: Application to change the register (PDF, 162KB)"){:rel="external"}
s2. Fill out either [form TR1 'Transfer of whole of registered title(s)' (PDF, 82KB)](http://www.landregistry.gov.uk/_media/downloads/forms/TR1.pdf "Form TR1: Transfer of whole of registered title(s) (PDF, 82KB)"){:rel="external"} if you're transferring your whole property or [form TP1 'Transfer of part of registered title(s)' (PDF, 101KB).](http://www.landregistry.gov.uk/_media/downloads/forms/TP1.pdf "Form TP1: Transfer of part of registered title(s) (PDF, 101KB)"){:rel="external"} if you're only transferring part of your property.
s3. If you're not a legal conveyancer, you need to enclose [form ID1 'Certificate of identity for a private individual' (PDF, 62KB).](http://www.landregistry.gov.uk/_media/downloads/forms/ID1.pdf "Form ID1: Certificate of identity for a private individual (PDF, 62KB)"){:rel="external"}  
s4. Enclose the [appropriate fee.](http://www.landregistry.gov.uk/professional/fees/fees-calculator "Land Registry fee calculator"){:rel="external"}
s5. Use [Land Registry’s office finder](http://www.landregistry.gov.uk/public/contacts/offices/office-finder "Land Registry office finder"){:rel="external"} to find out where to send your forms.
